      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay, so you're saying rebar is mainly there to handle the tension since concrete is bad at it. but what happens inside the slab if the tension gets too high and the concrete starts to fail? like, is there any kind of warning or does it just snap? also, you mentioned the rebar acts like a \"scaffold\" maybe you could explain how that helps keep the structure from just falling apart internally?",
      "source": "evaluator"
